Phase-2 chunk struct (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs ~788) — the plug point. Numpress adds a 7th field:
```csharp
private static StructField ChunkStructField() =>
    new StructField("chunk",
        new DataField<ulong>("spectrum_index"),
        new DataField<double>("mz_chunk_start"),
        new DataField<double>("mz_chunk_end"),
        new ListField("mz_chunk_values", new DataField<double>("item", true)),
        new DataField<string>("chunk_encoding"),
        new ListField("intensity", new DataField<float>("item", true)));
// Numpress mode adds: new ListField("mz_numpress_linear_bytes", new DataField<byte>("item")) // not null
```

CURIEs already in the writer (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs 60-62):
```csharp
private const string ChunkEncodingCurie  = "MS:1003089"; // delta (Phase-2 default; now --lossless)
private const string MzTransformCurie    = "MS:1003901"; // m/z anchor transform (unchanged in numpress)
private const string IntensityTransformCurie = "MS:1003902";
// ADD: private const string NumpressLinearCurie = "MS:1002312"; // numpress chunk_encoding + mz bytes transform
```

ChunkFacetStream.Append (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs ~963) builds one chunk row per window: it computes the
window slice, calls MzPeakChunkCodec.DeltaEncode -> start/end/values, sets _bEnc.Add(ChunkEncodingCurie),
emits mz_chunk_values (delta) + intensity. The numpress branch keeps start/end (true first/last m/z anchors),
sets encoding = NumpressLinearCurie, emits mz_chunk_values as a NULL row (parent-present, list-null via
MzPeakParquet.NullList — NOT EmptyList), and emits the numpress bytes row from MSNumpress.EncodeLinear(slice-as-double[]).

ChunkFacetStream.Flush (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs ~1007) writes columns via NestedLevels + WriteRowGroupAsync.
A numpress byte-list leaf is added the same way mz/intensity item leaves are (Leaf + ListOf + NestedLevels).

ChunkFooter / ChunkedSpectrumArrayIndex (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs 64-81, 437) — the footer const. Numpress
footer: entries 1-4 (start/end/values/encoding, MS:1003901, sorting_rank 0) UNCHANGED, KEEP the Phase-2
chunk.intensity entry (buffer_format chunk_secondary, MS:1003902, sorting_rank null) verbatim, INSERT a
chunk.mz_numpress_linear_bytes entry (buffer_format chunk_transform, transform MS:1002312, sorting_rank 0).
This is Option B (m/z-only numpress): 6 footer entries, NOT the reference's intensity-SLOF entry.

cv_list registration (MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs 268-273): the layout block calls CollectPrefix per CURIE; in
numpress mode register NumpressLinearCurie (MS:1002312) alongside the m/z/intensity transforms.

CLI (MainClass.cs ~597) + ParseInput (ParseInput.cs 111-147): MzPeakPointLayout (default false=chunked),
