    src/main/cpp/MSNumpress.cpp or the equivalent Java) for optimalLinearFixedPoint, encodeFixedPoint,
    decodeFixedPoint, encodeInt, decodeInt, encodeLinear, decodeLinear. Do NOT port from RESEARCH-port.md prose —
    that prose's "least-squares slope" and "5-byte values / continuation-varint" descriptions are WRONG; the
    canonical algorithm is max-value-based optimalLinearFixedPoint with 4-byte int32 first values and the encodeInt
    half-byte scheme. Match the reference's branch structure, masks (0xf0000000), and byte offsets (fp 0-7, values
    8-15, residuals 16+) exactly. Pure managed, AnyCPU — no P/Invoke, no x64-pinned APIs. Big-endian fixed-point
