<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 4: L2 round-trip + 3-mode validator 0/0 + size verification locks</name>
  <files>ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakChunkTests.cs</files>
  <action>
    Add NUnit locks (reuse Convert/PyArrow/ResolvePython/ResolveValidator; extend Convert to select numpress vs
    --lossless vs --point). Convert small.RAW in all three modes.

    (1) L2 m/z bound (ANTI-VACUITY HARDENED): decode our numpress m/z per chunk (read mz_chunk_start + mz_chunk_end +
    mz_numpress_linear_bytes via pyarrow; decode with the MzPeakChunkCodec numpress-decode helper / MSNumpress; drop the
    phantom leading value via the anchor rule), compare positionally to the SAME small.RAW converted with --lossless
    (Phase-2 proved bit-identical to source). The test MUST assert ALL of:
      - chunk count > 0 (the numpress spectra_data has at least one chunk row);
      - per chunk: the fixed point (decoded from the first 8 BE bytes) is finite AND > 0;
      - per chunk: decoded m/z length == that chunk's intensity length == that chunk's --lossless m/z length
        (no silent drops / mismatches);
      - 1- and 2-value chunks are guarded: do NOT index decoded[1] blindly; validate accordingly;
      - per chunk: BOTH the start anchor (decoded[0] ≈ mz_chunk_start) AND the end anchor
        (decoded[last] ≈ mz_chunk_end) are within 0.5/fp_used;
      - total compared m/z count across all chunks == the archive's spectrum_data_point_count (no chunk skipped,
        no values dropped);
      - max|Δm/z| <= 0.5/fp_used per chunk (using the SAME per-chunk fp the encoder used), worst-case ~4.63e-7 Th.
    (2) Intensity bit-exact: numpress intensity list == --lossless intensity list bitwise (SingleToInt32Bits),
    0 mismatches. (3) --lossless and --point remain BITWISE-L1: keep/extend the Phase-2 bitwise-multiset lock so both
    modes still match source exactly. (4) Schema/footer: numpress spectra_data has 7 fields incl mz_numpress_linear_bytes;
    chunk_encoding == MS:1002312; mz_chunk_values null_count == row count with ZERO present/empty lists (assert null,
    not zero-length); footer mz_numpress_linear_bytes entry has buffer_format chunk_transform + transform MS:1002312 +
    sorting_rank 0; intensity entry unchanged. (5) Validator: mzpeak-validate 0 errors on all THREE archives (numpress
    default, --lossless, --point); Ignore when validator absent. (6) Size: numpress spectra_data.parquet bytes <
    --lossless (delta) spectra_data.parquet bytes. BOM-free; compact; no harness/phase comments.
  </action>
  <verify>
    <automated>DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=LatestMajor DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD_TO_PRERELEASE=1 arch -arm64 dotnet test ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/ThermoRawFileParserTest.csproj -c Release</automated>
  </verify>
  <done>Full suite green native arm64: chunk count > 0; per-chunk fp finite & > 0; per-chunk decoded length == intensity == lossless length; total compared count == spectrum_data_point_count; both start and end anchors validated; numpress m/z within 0.5/fp vs lossless; intensity bit-exact; mz_chunk_values null (zero present/empty); --lossless/--point bitwise-L1; validator 0/0 in all three modes; numpress spectra_data smaller than delta. (NP-04, VER for NP-01..03)</done>
</task>

</tasks>

<threat_model>
## Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| RAW scan data → numpress encoder | Untrusted/variable m/z arrays (empty, single-point, near-equal, non-monotone) cross into the codec |
| vendored ms-numpress source → assembly | Third-party algorithm ported into our managed assembly |
| numpress bytes → archive consumers | Lossy m/z bytes must be self-describing (transform CURIE) for downstream readers |

## STRIDE Threat Register

| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| T-03-01 | Tampering | Numpress encode/decode correctness | mitigate | Faithful line-for-line canonical port + exact vectors V1-V4 (OptimalLinearFixedPoint([1,2,3])==1073741823, reference row-0 fp==10599266.0, byte-identity vs ms-numpress test vector AND vs pynumpress encode) + per-chunk anti-vacuity L2 bound assertion (Tasks 1,4) |
| T-03-02 | Tampering | x64 dependency reintroduction | mitigate | Pure-managed AnyCPU port (System only); explicit AnyCPU/MSIL assembly assertion in tests (Task 1) |
| T-03-03 | Information disclosure | Self-describing transform | mitigate | MS:1002312 recorded in array_index footer + cv_list + data_processing lossy note (Task 2) |
| T-03-04 | Denial of service | Pathological m/z slices (empty/single/2/near-equal) | mitigate | Codec edge-case tests; encoder must terminate on all slice lengths; short-chunk guards in decode (Tasks 1,2) |
| T-03-05 | Repudiation | --lossless/--point silently lossy | accept→mitigate | Bitwise-L1 locks keep both modes exact; CLI warning only in numpress mode (Tasks 3,4) |
| T-03-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | n/a | No package-manager installs introduced; ms-numpress is vendored source, not a package; python3.11/pynumpress used only as a test oracle (pre-existing on system) |
</threat_model>

