.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-PLAN.md:359:- **Numpress port correctness / L2 bound (chief):** the encodeInt 4-bit half-byte residual scheme and the 4-byte LE int32 first-value packing are the easiest places to mis-port — and the RESEARCH-port.md PROSE actively misleads (it claims least-squares slope + 5-byte values / continuation-varint nibbles, all wrong). The executor MUST port from the canonical reference source, not the prose. Mitigated by the exact vectors: OptimalLinearFixedPoint([1,2,3])==1073741823, reference row-0 fp==10599266.0, and BYTE-IDENTITY vs both the ms-numpress test vector and pynumpress encode at a shared fp (not merely decode-within-bound), plus the per-chunk anti-vacuity 0.5/fp decode assertion. The phantom-leading-value decode artifact is handled in the codec's anchor-aligned decode helper (with short-chunk guards), not the raw codec.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-PLAN.md:364:- **Vacuous L2 pass:** a bad decode or silent drop could compare fewer/zero values and trivially pass a naive bound. Mitigated by the Task-4 anti-vacuity guards (chunk count > 0, per-chunk + total length parity vs spectrum_data_point_count, both start/end anchors, short-chunk guards).
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/REVIEW-codex.md:1:- BLOCKER, [.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-PLAN.md:148](/Users/kohlbach/Claude/mzPeak4TRFR/.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-PLAN.md:148): MSNumpress algorithm spec is incorrect/incomplete. `optimalLinearFixedPoint` is described as least-squares slope-based, and residual packing is described in [RESEARCH-port.md:71](/Users/kohlbach/Claude/mzPeak4TRFR/.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/RESEARCH-port.md:71) as continuation-varint nibbles; canonical/pynumpress behavior differs. Fix: replace the prose with direct canonical `optimalLinearFixedPoint`, `encodeInt`, and `decodeInt` pseudocode/source-port requirements, and add fixed-point vectors such as `[1,2,3] -> 1073741823`, known vector byte identity, and reference row0 fp `10599266.0`.
.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/REVIEW-codex.md:5:- MEDIUM, [.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-PLAN.md:243](/Users/kohlbach/Claude/mzPeak4TRFR/.planning/phases/03-numpress-linear-mz/03-01-PLAN.md:243): L2 bound test lacks anti-vacuity guards. A bad decode/drop could compare fewer or no values, and the phantom-drop helper can index `decoded[1]` on short chunks. Fix: assert chunk count > 0, fp finite > 0, decoded length equals intensity/lossless length per chunk, total compared count equals `spectrum_data_point_count`, and guard single/two-value chunks while validating both start and end anchors.

